## Analysis of the Main Target Image

The target structure consists of 2 building blocks arranged in 2 layers:
1. **Bottom Layer**: A red block that appears to be a horizontal piece with two semi-circular cutouts on top. This red piece forms the base of the structure.
2. **Top Layer**: A blue cube placed on top of the red base, specifically positioned on one of the semi-circular cutouts of the base.

## Spatial Relationships
- The red base block is oriented horizontally with two semi-circular cutouts facing upward
- The blue cube sits directly on top of the middle section of the red base (on one of the cutouts)

## Selection of Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on my analysis, I need the following blocks:
1. A red piece with two cutouts (appears to match block #3)
2. A blue cube (appears to match block #9)

## Assembly Order

```
{
   Step1: Move block with index 3
   Step2: Move block with index 9
}
```

The assembly process involves first placing the red base block (#3) and then positioning the blue cube (#9) on top of one of the semi-circular cutouts of the base.
